@startuml django_diagrama_de_secuencia
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true
skinparam maxMessageSize 200
skinparam shadowing false

title Diagrama de Secuencia - Flujo de Peticion HTTP en Django
caption Framework Django (MTV) - Ciclo Request/Response

actor "Cliente\n(Browser)" as Client
participant "Web Server\n(Gunicorn/uWSGI)" as Server
participant "WSGIHandler\n(Front Controller)" as WSGI
participant "Middleware\nChain" as Middleware
participant "URLResolver\n(Dispatcher)" as URLResolver
participant "View\n(Controller)" as View
participant "Template\nEngine" as Template
participant "Model\n(ORM)" as Model
database "Database" as DB

== Fase 1: Recepción de la Petición ==

Client -> Server: HTTP Request\n(GET /articles/1/)
activate Server

Server -> WSGI: __call__(environ, start_response)
activate WSGI

note right of WSGI
    El WSGIHandler actúa como
    Front Controller, punto de
    entrada único para todas
    las peticiones
end note

WSGI -> WSGI: Crear HttpRequest\ndesde environ
create "HttpRequest" as Request
WSGI -> Request: new HttpRequest(environ)

== Fase 2: Cadena de Middleware (Request) ==

WSGI -> Middleware: get_response(request)
activate Middleware

note over Middleware
    Los middlewares se ejecutan en
    orden según MIDDLEWARE setting
end note

group Middleware Request Phase
    Middleware -> Middleware: SecurityMiddleware\n.process_request(request)
    Middleware -> Middleware: SessionMiddleware\n.process_request(request)
    note right: Carga sesión en request.session
    Middleware -> Middleware: AuthenticationMiddleware\n.process_request(request)
    note right: Carga usuario en request.user
    Middleware -> Middleware: CsrfViewMiddleware\n.process_request(request)
end

== Fase 3: URL Routing (Dispatcher) ==

Middleware -> URLResolver: resolve(request.path)
activate URLResolver

URLResolver -> URLResolver: Match path against\nurl_patterns
URLResolver -> URLResolver: Extract view_func,\nargs, kwargs

create "ResolverMatch" as Match
URLResolver -> Match: new ResolverMatch(\nfunc, args, kwargs, url_name)
URLResolver --> Middleware: ResolverMatch
deactivate URLResolver

== Fase 4: Middleware View Phase ==

group Middleware View Phase
    Middleware -> Middleware: CsrfViewMiddleware\n.process_view(request, view_func,\nview_args, view_kwargs)
    note right: Valida CSRF token
end

== Fase 5: Ejecución de la View ==

Middleware -> View: view_func(request, *args, **kwargs)
activate View

note right of View
    La View en Django es el
    equivalente al Controller
    en MVC tradicional
end note

alt Class-Based View
    View -> View: dispatch(request, *args, **kwargs)
    View -> View: get(request, *args, **kwargs)
end

== Fase 6: Interacción con el Modelo (ORM) ==

View -> Model: objects.get(pk=1)
activate Model

Model -> Model: Manager.get_queryset()
Model -> Model: QuerySet.filter(pk=1)
Model -> DB: SELECT * FROM articles WHERE id=1
activate DB
DB --> Model: Row data
deactivate DB

Model -> Model: Hydrate Model instance
Model --> View: Article instance
deactivate Model

== Fase 7: Preparación del Contexto ==

View -> View: get_context_data(\nobject=article)

note right of View
    El contexto contiene los datos
    que serán pasados al template
end note

== Fase 8: Renderizado del Template ==

View -> Template: render_to_string(\n'article_detail.html', context)
activate Template

Template -> Template: Engine.get_template(\n'article_detail.html')
Template -> Template: Loader.load_template()

note right of Template
    El Template en Django es la
    capa de presentación (View en MVC)
end note

Template -> Template: Template.render(\nRequestContext(request, context))

group Template Processing
    Template -> Template: Parse template nodes
    Template -> Template: Resolve variables\nfrom context
    Template -> Template: Execute template tags
    Template -> Template: Apply filters
end

Template --> View: HTML string
deactivate Template

== Fase 9: Creación de la Response ==

View -> View: Create HttpResponse\nwith rendered content

create "HttpResponse" as Response
View -> Response: new HttpResponse(\ncontent, content_type,\nstatus=200)

View --> Middleware: HttpResponse
deactivate View

== Fase 10: Cadena de Middleware (Response) ==

group Middleware Response Phase
    note over Middleware
        Middlewares se ejecutan en
        orden inverso para Response
    end note

    Middleware -> Middleware: CsrfViewMiddleware\n.process_response(request, response)
    Middleware -> Middleware: AuthenticationMiddleware\n.process_response(request, response)
    Middleware -> Middleware: SessionMiddleware\n.process_response(request, response)
    note right: Guarda cambios en sesión
    Middleware -> Middleware: SecurityMiddleware\n.process_response(request, response)
    note right: Añade headers de seguridad\n(X-Frame-Options, etc.)
end

Middleware --> WSGI: HttpResponse
deactivate Middleware

== Fase 11: Envío de la Respuesta ==

WSGI -> WSGI: start_response(\nstatus, response_headers)
WSGI --> Server: [response.content]
deactivate WSGI

Server --> Client: HTTP Response\n(200 OK + HTML)
deactivate Server

== Flujo Alternativo: Error Handling ==

note over WSGI, View
    **Manejo de Excepciones:**

    1. View lanza excepción (ej: Http404)
    2. Middlewares reciben process_exception()
    3. Si ninguno maneja, Django busca
       handler404/handler500 en urls.py
    4. Se renderiza template de error
    5. Response pasa por middleware chain
end note

@enduml


